info.title: Broker WebSockets
info.description: Real-time broker data streaming for orders, positions, and executions

subscribe.summary: The API user can receive a given message from the server.

publish.summary: The API user can send a given message to the server.

BrokerConnectionStatus.description:
Broker connection status

Represents the connection state between the backend and the real broker.
Status values: 1 = Connected, 0 = Disconnected
BrokerConnectionStatus.title: BrokerConnectionStatus

BrokerConnectionSubscriptionRequest.description: WebSocket subscription request for broker connection status updates
BrokerConnectionSubscriptionRequest.title: BrokerConnectionSubscriptionRequest

EquityData.description:
Equity and balance data for account

Represents the current financial state of an account including
balance, equity, and profit/loss values.
EquityData.title: EquityData

EquitySubscriptionRequest.description: WebSocket subscription request for equity/balance updates
EquitySubscriptionRequest.title: EquitySubscriptionRequest

ExecutionSubscriptionRequest.title: ExecutionSubscriptionRequest

OrderStatus.title: OrderStatus

OrderSubscriptionRequest.title: OrderSubscriptionRequest

OrderType.description: Order type enumeration matching TradingView OrderType
OrderType.title: OrderType

PlacedOrder.description:
Complete order with status (matching TradingView PlacedOrder/PlacedOrderBase)
Contains information about a placed order

avgPrice.description: Average fulfilled price for the order
avgPrice.title: Avgprice

updateTime.description: Last update time (unix timestamp in milliseconds)
updateTime.title: Updatetime

PlacedOrder.title: PlacedOrder

Position.description:
Position data (matching TradingView Position/PositionBase)
Describes a single position

Note: qty can be 0 when a position is closed. TradingView expects
positionUpdate with qty=0 to confirm position closure within 10 seconds,
otherwise it shows "Position closing timeout" error.

qty.description: Position quantity (0 when closed, positive otherwise)
qty.title: Qty

avgPrice.description: Weighted average price of all positions for a symbol (used for position line on chart)
avgPrice.title: Avgprice

Position.title: Position

PositionSubscriptionRequest.description: WebSocket subscription request for position updates
PositionSubscriptionRequest.title: PositionSubscriptionRequest

Side.description: Order/Position side enumeration matching TradingView Side
Side.title: Side

StopType.description: Stop type enumeration matching TradingView StopType
StopType.title: StopType
